15/05/2005
BANJA LUKA, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- The Republika Srpska (RS) government submitted bail guarantees to the UN war crimes tribunal Friday (13 May) for Bosnian Serb Mitar Rasevic, who commanded guards at a camp in Foca from 1992-1995. Rasevic, charged with crimes against humanity committed against Muslim and Croat inmates, surrendered to the tribunal in August 2003. 
Also Friday, RS announced that the entity budget for this year envisions 102,092 euros in assistance to war crimes indictees who have surrendered and to their families. Some 18,000 euros was allocated in the first quarter of the year. (PBS BiH, Nezavisne novine - 14/05/05)
